      "instruction": "<p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> with 450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[675ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[900ml]</span> <strong>boiled water  </strong>and the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potato & sweet</strong> <strong>potato</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong>, then bring to boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-18 min or until the potatoes are tender</p><p>Tip: Stir occasionally to stop it sticking!</p>",
